28/08/2007
PARIS, France -- In a speech to his diplomatic corps on Monday (August 27th), President Nicholas Sarkozy said France supports the supervised independence of Kosovo.
Presenting his platform for foreign policy to the country's ambassadors, Sarkozy stressed that this model, implemented with the help of the EU, will guarantee that the rights of minorities in Kosovo are protected.
(RFE, Telegrafi, Kosovapress, Top-Channel, Tanjug - 27/08/07)
